    <h4 class="about-sub-heading"> About Alleppey</h4>


        <div>
           Alleppey is a more commonly known name of a district in Kerala called Alappuzha. It is one of the oldest cities of Kerala built along the Arabian coastline, situated around 65 Kms south of Kochi and around 150 Kms north of Thiruvananthapuram. Alleppey, also called “Venice of the East”, is majorly known for its beautiful backwaters which pass through local villages extending to the Punnamada Lake which itself flows into the Arabian Sea. Alleppey also has beautiful beaches and lagoons and to top it all, it’s extremely peaceful and non-crowded place, best to enjoy a nice relaxing holiday. Alleppey is also home to Ayurvedic spas and organic spices like other major Kerala cities.
        </div>

            
